                <h1>Sylvia Plath: Iconic Poet and Novelist</h1>
                <p>Sylvia Plath was an iconic American poet and novelist, renowned for her confessional style and profound emotional depth. Born in 1932, her work often explored themes of mental illness, identity, and feminism. Plath's most famous work, "The Bell Jar," and her poetry collection, "Ariel," continue to resonate, reflecting her struggle with depression and the search for self.</p>
